This is a super simple, yet powerful way to deploy your jekyll site using Textmate. 

INSTALLATION

git clone git://github.com/arnklint/jekyll-tmbundle.git

Open the Jekyll.tmbundle 
Put the _tasks directory in your local jekyll siteÂ´s root. 
Modify the up shellscript (set the user credentials and server info)
Press CMD + SHIFT + J in textmate when editing your jekyll site. Done!

